    "parent_section": "Executive summary",
    "content_preview": "Understanding, estimating and reporting on tax expenditures is an important exercise in public financial management. Tax",
    "content_hash": "1d70bfe0523bc89ffb389b57c8dd7002ee81986323d084f2d954eab269efb4ba"
  },
  {
    "chunk_type": "paragraph",
    "page_refs": [
      4
    ],
    "parent_section": "Executive summary",
    "content_preview": "This report uses shipment-level microdata from the Ethiopian Customs Commission to estimate import tax expenditures for ",
    "content_hash": "0797620962bbb45c539005018fb0637c941c1836316ab2fa115c48688626a968"
  },
  {
    "chunk_type": "paragraph",
    "page_refs": [
      4
    ],
    "parent_section": "Executive summary",
    "content_preview": "Where appropriate, exemptions and rate reductions are considered separately, and estimates are presented for different c",
    "content_hash": "55f82482c68fba45057d5598d7f85e2d70f4bc6e175fdd48b0797ebacb94efb0"
  },
  {
    "chunk_type": "paragraph",
    "page_refs": [
      4
    ],
    "parent_section": "Executive summary",
    "content_preview": "The report uses the revenue forgone method and does not attempt to incorporate the behavioural or compliance effects of ",
    "content_hash": "ee53e0849b9a264740b420bd17edc5c1cf049293a19e01e8a2711aab1244f81a"
  },
  {
    "chunk_type": "paragraph",
    "page_refs": [
      4
    ],
    "parent_section": "Executive summary",
    "content_preview": "Import tax expenditures were ETB 120.7 billion in FY 2020/21, which represented around 2.8% of GDP, between ETB 76.4 bil",
    "content_hash": "4b99a2e634ac925815d7e700c8fe680ac7ad6fd2358903158cca846605f53433"
  },
  {
    "chunk_type": "paragraph",
    "page_refs": [
      5
    ],
    "parent_section": "Executive summary",
    "content_preview": "import value of affected goods in FY 2020/21, 16% in FY 2019/20 and around 20% in FY 2018/19.",
    "content_hash": "a88c5e6e03315f6883ee6e078ea83e42cb9b4fdcb0d4f26bb0809f8afa43964a"
  },
  {
    "chunk_type": "paragraph",
    "page_refs": [
      5
    ],
    "parent_section": "Executive summary",
    "content_preview": "In FY 2020/21, import tax expenditures were especially large on motor vehicles and on animal and vegetable fats. Togethe",
    "content_hash": "c512a9fda795ce28e8c19580b2f301428b72c6d3727cc875f2871ff3cb71d471"
  },
  {
    "chunk_type": "paragraph",
    "page_refs": [
      5
    ],
    "parent_section": "Executive summary",
    "content_preview": "Tax exemptions for capital and investment goods and 'second schedule' preferential customs and surtax rates respectively",
    "content_hash": "cce96df44d7e1940ae13d46150e39b4397e0e8dde575a72482f543647ef0fa9f"
  }
